The fire broke out in the Tsitsikamma section on Friday and was extinguished before it could reach the forest areas. CAPE TOWN - Authorities are investigating the cause of a fire at the Garden Route National Park which left two buildings gutted.The fire broke out in the Tsitsikamma section on Friday and was extinguished before it could reach the forest areas.The blaze reportedly started in the kitchen of the Tsitsikamma Restaurant.SANParks spokesperson Nandi Mgwadlamba says the restaurant and curio shop burned down. It has been burnt down completely, but the rest of the park is safe and open. The cause of the fire is still under investigation. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)